 >> Anonymous Tue Aug 11 08:01:35 2020 No.11996822 >>11996529> in other words: any number whose square equals -1 is the imaginary unitNo. One of them is the imaginary unit, the other is its negation. Similar to how i^2=1 has 1 and -1 as its solutions. Except that 1 and -1 are distinguished by the fact that 1 is the multiplicative unit, i.e. 1*x=x, whereas -1 isn't. There is no such distinction for i vs -i, nor does it matter.
