# struct.node.disp.global

Syntax

m := struct.node.disp.global(sn<,i>)

Get the displacement of structure node expressed in a global system.

Returns: m - matrix of displacement with all degrees-of-freedom if the argument i is not assigned, or displacement at the ith degree-of-freedom if the argument i is assigned. sn - pointer to the structure node i - degree-of-freedom, i ∈ {1, 2, … , 6}. The default is 1.
