$$\phi(g_1 g_2) = (g_1 g_2)^2 = g_1^2 g_2^2 = \phi(g_1)\phi(g_2)$$

$$\phi(1_G) = 1_G^2 = 1_G$$

$$\phi(g_1^{-1})=(g_1^{-1})^2 = g_1^{-2}$$

$$\phi(g_1 g_2)^{-1} = (g_1 g_2)^{-2} = g_2^{-2} g_1^{-2} = \phi(g_2^{-1})\phi(g_1^{-1})$$

$$\phi(g^0) = (g^0)^2 = g^0 = 1_G$$

$$\phi(g g^{-1}) = (g g^{-1})^2 = g^2 g^{-2} = 1_G$$

